				"id": "ALAS-2015-519",
				"title": "Amazon Linux AMI 2014.03 - ALAS-2015-519: medium priority package update for xorg-x11-server",
				"description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux AMI that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2015-0255:\n\tA buffer over-read flaw was found in the way the X.Org server handled XkbGetGeometry requests. A malicious, authorized client could use this flaw to disclose portions of the X.Org server memory, or cause the X.Org server to crash using a specially crafted XkbGetGeometry request.\n",
